The interwebs are crazy. And Safaricom is there to respond to the craziness in kind. One user of the Telecommunication services reached out to the online customer care team on Facebook and asked for help. Ray Rash asked for help - ever so politely - using sheng. Actually, using the even more corrupted version of sheng called Shembeteng. For those who don't understand Shembeteng, Ray was asking,Â "Hi Safaricom, niko na shida kidogo. Mtu akitaka kureplace simcard hueda wapi? (Hi Safaricom, I have a small issue. Where can I go to replace my sim card?)" Safaricom responded in fluent Shembeteng, here is a translation,Â "Enda duka yoyote yetu na ID yako, Ray. ^MZ. (Go to any of our shots with your ID, Ray.)" Here are some reactions from the ever undefeated people of the internet. Laroh Tonui Cholyo:Â Safaricom nakulombotov leo tu. Stanley Cheruiyot:Â Safaricom PLC should now be disbanded and everyone to go home ğŸ˜‚ ğŸ˜‚ ğŸ˜‚ ğŸ˜‚ John Gikuru:Â Safarimbiticom mnajumbataako hii lumbatagha ua ubwakini Cate Catrina:Â ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚huyu admin wenyu ni mnomare Felix Owino Jr.:Â ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ i have not laughed before ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ Ben Manyore:Â Alah nani admin Bosibori Moruri:Â I'd never laughed this loud!ğŸ˜ğŸ˜ğŸ˜ Oliver Nyanducha:Â Kwisha waTz hawatatuelewa tena Faith Mwikali:Â Wueh, hadi 'see translation' wako nje pia. Timoh Ngeera:Â Please shun this dirty language ğŸ˜­ it will have negative impact to our Young ones Reply4h Kipng'enoh Elvis ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£ Arch Dennis Nyagah HomesBuild:Â These are the dudes that will Come to ask for our daughter's hand in marriage after 20 years.... I hope someone is not kidding Zettyline Nafula:Â ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£safaricom pia hujionea mambo ...mimi nilical juzi kuwasalimia tu Mary Mutheu Mweu:Â Aki hii ni kikamba ya majuuğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ Fred Fred:Â Sheng evolving faster than anything else. Even youths themselves cant keep up Lynn Mosonik:Â #legalize weed.